result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Transcript of Plea/Sentencing Hearing held 7/24/17

ADA Melissa Inlow appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person, in custody, with Attorney Poss.  Defendant plead guilty to Counts 1 and 3 in 16CF115.   The parties will recommend this sentence be consecutive to 10CF170.  All remaining charges in 16CF115, plus all charges in 15CF202 and 16CF6 are dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 24, 2017 at 10:00 am.
DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared through Attorney Poss.  Schedule plea with JA.
Status conference on June 12, 2017 at 03:00 pm.

WOPH on 16CF6, 16CF115, 15CF202:  

Defendant appears in person in custody from Dodge Correctional with counsel SPD William Poss.  Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Defendant will be waiving his right to a preliminary hearing on all 3 cases.  Informations have been sent electronically by the State.  Court performs a colloquy regarding his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant does wish to waive that right on all 3 cases.  Court finds he FVKI waives his right to a preliminary hearing and he is bound over for trial.  Defense waives the reading of the Informations and defendant stands mute on all charges.  Court enters NGP on all charges.  SPD Poss states they have been in negotiations but the State is waiting for a report from an officer yet.  DA Fox will contact the officer.  STC on all 3 cases on 6-12-17 at 3:00 p.m.  Defendant will not need to be present.
